Uploading: Another Fun Rus Parody 6 Songs Translated into English.
It is becoming a fun thing for me to do. :-] Still it is a time consuming process, but now I did it little faster. I hope that is because of getting experienced rather than being in haste with reducing quality of translation. So be my judge, see how fun are those songs and how understandable they are.

Today songs are:
.1. o_s_p  football - about wife who is troubled because her husband's top priority is to play football with his friends;
.2. o_s_p  obsessed - about woman experiencing unwanted attention from unusual follower;
.3. pushnoy  leopoldium - Pushnoy is guy, who likes to transform any song into hard rock version. This song originally was in russian cartoon about adventures of cat Leopold who was kind and polite (not like this Mr. Moose I've described in my jokes) and was bullied by two mice. So this song is some kind of hymn of bicycle rider. And thanks to Pushnoy this song sounds like really very serious and determined heavy metal guy on his bicycle;
.4. pushnoy  mind_crazy - oh, that one is special. Pushnoy took some very old song (time of vinyl records and ussr still existing) and just made fun of it in his stile; 
.5. red_mould_00_goodye_usa - this one is about guy who caused nuclear apocalypse because of employer didn't pay him for his work;
.6. red_mould_16_narco - song about junkie and one of his hallucinations.

Songs (except two from Pushnoy) are parodies. I mean, there were original songs with original lyrics. Then, some humorists took the song, created different lyrics with whole new meaning. Songs can remind you original one, but text is ridiculous.

As usual, to watch those songs, you may need to rename zip to 7z, unpack 6 mkv files from it. Mkv files have english srt inside.
